narratives.question_text: Use the space below to comment on questions 1-10, if you wish
comments: This class should only be taken to those who are really open to the self reflective practitioner development required of it. The class will be frustrating and too loose for those without some previous interest in the concepts addressed.
Open dialogue between students and professor.
Journaling, self presentations, David Madson
The readings were fantastic and the course provided an open and safe arena to talk about deeper issues and delve into what we are trying to accomplish as professionals.

narratives.question_text: The things about this course most in need of improvement are:
comments: More time to talk about the subject matter.
sometimes the readings weren't covered very rigorously and we repeated discussion of a lot of concepts that could have been nuanced by returning to the readings more closely.

Awesome!

narratives.question_text: Discuss if you wish how this course fits into your overall program.
comments: This is a great foundational course for students who want to explore important issues at the foundation of the environmental management/forestry degrees.
I took this as a long term investment in my professional health and reflexivity - it was not really required and i'll be sad that I don;t have many more credits to put toward this type of course use.
